{
  "texts": [
    "The principal reason is that topic models depend on the word co-occurrence information to infer latent topics, but such information is extremely sparse in short texts due to their limited context.",
    "This challenge, referred to as data sparsity (Yan et al 2013; Wu and Li 2019), hinders topic models from discovering high-quality topics and thus has attracted considerable attention in the research community.",
    "Several studies are proposed to overcome this data sparsity challenge.",
    "Lin et al (2020) use the Archimedean copulas to regularize the discreteness of topic distributions of short texts.",
    "Wu et al (2020b) propose to quantize doc-topic distributions of short texts to quantization vectors following the idea of Van den Oord and Vinyals (2017)."
  ]
}